on.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-jeff-bezos-ex-wife-mackenzie-scott-my-approach-to-philanthropy-will-continue-to-be-thoughtful-it-will-take-time-and-effort-and-care-but-why-thoughtful-generosity-should-never-be-delayed/articleshow/132347658.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-jeff-bezos-ex-wife-mackenzie-scott-my-approach-to-philanthropy-will-continue-to-be-thoughtful-it-will-take-time-and-effort-and-care-but-why-thoughtful-generosity-should-never-be-delayed/articleshow/132347658.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T20:41:25+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132347696,imgsize-65750.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['So sweet I'll read it twice': Iran celebrates Graham's death as Trump, Netanyahu mourn]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132346568.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/so-sweet-ill-read-it-twice-iran-celebrates-grahams-death-as-trump-netanyahu-mourn/articleshow/132346568.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/so-sweet-ill-read-it-twice-iran-celebrates-grahams-death-as-trump-netanyahu-mourn/articleshow/132346568.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T19:47:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132347049,imgsize-90104.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Who was the masked man?' Khamenei funeral mystery solved]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132346181.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/who-was-the-masked-man-khamenei-funeral-mystery-solved/articleshow/132346181.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/who-was-the-masked-man-khamenei-funeral-mystery-solved/articleshow/132346181.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T19:17:36+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132346278,imgsize-170830.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists finally know why gold never tarnishes, and the secret lies in its self-protecting surface]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132345906.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Recent scientific research has revealed that the surface atoms of gold can rearrange themselves to create a protective barrier against oxidation. This extraordinary natural mechanism significantly reduces tarnishing rates by up to a trillion times, ensuring gold retains its radiant luster. This discovery opens up possibilities for industrial applications, allowing gold to be utilized as an even more efficient catalyst.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-finally-know-why-gold-never-tarnishes-and-the-secret-lies-in-its-self-protecting-surface/articleshow/132345906.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-finally-know-why-gold-never-tarnishes-and-the-secret-lies-in-its-self-protecting-surface/articleshow/132345906.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T19:16:01+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132346544,imgsize-175826.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[24-year-old woman killed, man injured in West London stabbing; Suspect, 44, arrested on suspicion of murder]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132345989.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/24-year-old-woman-killed-man-injured-in-west-london-stabbing-suspect-44-arrested-on-suspicion-of-murder/articleshow/132345989.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/24-year-old-woman-killed-man-injured-in-west-london-stabbing-suspect-44-arrested-on-suspicion-of-murder/articleshow/132345989.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T18:33:30+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132346106,imgsize-561445.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How floating solar panels created a new home for thousands of salmon at a Chile fish farm]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132341422.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Chilean salmon farm replaced diesel generators with floating solar panels. This initiative significantly cut emissions and fuel consumption annually. The new system also created a quieter and more sheltered environment for the fish. Thousands of salmon have now gathered beneath the floating solar structures. This project demonstrates renewable energy's unexpected environmental benefits beyond emission reduction]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-floating-solar-panels-created-a-new-home-for-thousands-of-salmon-at-a-chile-fish-farm/articleshow/132341422.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-floating-solar-panels-created-a-new-home-for-thousands-of-salmon-at-a-chile-fish-farm/articleshow/132341422.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T13:08:16+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132346128,imgsize-160663.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UAE sends nationwide alert after detecting missile threats outside borders]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132346547.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-sends-nationwide-alert-as-air-defences-respond-authorities-say-missile-threats-stayed-outside-countrys-borders/articleshow/132346547.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-sends-nationwide-alert-as-air-defences-respond-authorities-say-missile-threats-stayed-outside-countrys-borders/articleshow/132346547.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T19:19:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132346722,imgsize-43170.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia hacked cameras near NATO bases to monitor Ukraine arms: Report]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132345306.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russia-hacked-cameras-near-nato-bases-to-monitor-ukraine-arms-report/articleshow/132345306.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russia-hacked-cameras-near-nato-bases-to-monitor-ukraine-arms-report/articleshow/132345306.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T18:14:31+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132345907,imgsize-51162.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ken Griffin's $250 million superyacht wouldn't fit at his mansion, so he built a private marina]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132345318.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Billionaire Ken Griffin is advocating for amendments to Miami Beach's zoning laws to permit a private helipad, enhancing his luxurious portfolio that already includes a private marina and superyacht facility. The proposed helipad, situated on industrially designated land, is strategically distanced from residential neighborhoods. This request exclusively pertains to Terminal Island, where current regulations prohibit private helipads, aiming to establish a private transportation hub for the Citadel founder.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/billionaire-ken-griffins-250-million-superyacht-wouldnt-fit-at-his-mansion-so-he-built-a-3-7-acre-private-marina-in-miami-now-he-wants-a-private-helipad-and-fly-in-to-avoid-rush-hour-traffic/articleshow/132345318.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/billionaire-ken-griffins-250-million-superyacht-wouldnt-fit-at-his-mansion-so-he-built-a-3-7-acre-private-marina-in-miami-now-he-wants-a-private-helipad-and-fly-in-to-avoid-rush-hour-traffic/articleshow/132345318.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T18:12:43+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132345806,imgsize-196092.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['I left America after H-1B stamping trip': Indian professional explains why he returned home and what he struggled with]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132343769.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An Indian professional shared his voluntary return from the US after an H-1B visa stamping trip. He found closer family ties and easier professional networking opportunities upon his return. However, he also faced significant infrastructure and traffic issues in India. Business processes and pollution presented further daily challenges for him. Despite these difficulties, he felt his decision to return was the right one.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/i-left-america-after-h-1b-stamping-trip-indian-professional-explains-why-he-returned-home-and-what-he-struggled-with/articleshow/132343769.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/i-left-america-after-h-1b-stamping-trip-indian-professional-explains-why-he-returned-home-and-what-he-struggled-with/articleshow/132343769.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T19:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132343887,imgsize-69485.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This routine US Navy training mission near California turned into one of the most discussed UFO cases in recent history]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132344608.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A 2004 US Navy training mission encountered an unexplained aerial object. Pilots and radar operators observed a peculiar "Tic Tac" shaped craft. Infrared video footage later surfaced, adding to the mystery. This incident gained widespread attention after a 2017 New York Times report. The Pentagon has not provided a definitive explanation for the sighting.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-routine-us-navy-training-mission-near-california-turned-into-one-of-the-most-discussed-ufo-cases-in-recent-history/articleshow/132344608.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-routine-us-navy-training-mission-near-california-turned-into-one-of-the-most-discussed-ufo-cases-in-recent-history/articleshow/132344608.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T17:49:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132344644,imgsize-41361.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Ralph Waldo Emerson: 'What you do speaks so loudly that I cannot hear what you say']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132340319.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[True character shines through actions, often more so than mere words. It is through consistent behaviour that we forge trust and earn respect from those around us. Integrity is the harmony between what one says and what one does. Effective leadership succeeds by modelling positive behaviour for others to follow. In essence, our daily actions, not just bold proclamations, shape our reputations.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-ralph-waldo-emerson-what-you-do-speaks-so-loudly-that-i-cannot-hear-what-you-say/articleshow/132340319.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-ralph-waldo-emerson-what-you-do-speaks-so-loudly-that-i-cannot-hear-what-you-say/articleshow/132340319.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T16:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132341254,imgsize-234430.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Qatar declares 4 days of mourning, suspends public sector work over death of for